OL,6,FThe Environment Agency attributed a
OL,7,Frise in pollution incidents last year
OL,8,Fto persistent underinvestment in new
OL,9,Finfrastructure, poor asset
OL,10,Fmaintenance, and reduced resilience
OL,11,Fbecause of the impacts of climate
OL,12,Fchange.
OL,14,FIt is understood the agency is still
OL,15,Finvestigating the incidents and their
OL,16,Fcauses more closely to understand the
OL,17,Fmajor increase from 2023, and decide
OL,18,Fon any action.
